cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper deals with the emergence of structured language in neural agents, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically neural networks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the advantages of compositional language in neural agents, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a probabilistic model of neural iterated learning, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
